ENTRY       EC 2.3.1.230                Enzyme
NAME        2-heptyl-4(1H)-quinolone synthase
CLASS       Transferases;
            Acyltransferases;
            Transferring groups other than aminoacyl groups
SYSNAME     malonyl-CoA:anthraniloyl-CoA C-acetyltransferase (decarboxylating)
REACTION    (1) 3-oxodecanoate + anthraniloyl-CoA = CoA + 2-heptyl-4(1H)-quinolone + CO2 + H2O [RN:R10589];
            (2) malonyl-CoA + anthraniloyl-CoA = 2 CoA + 4-hydroxy-2(1H)-quinolone + CO2 [RN:R10590]
ALL_REAC    R10589 R10590
SUBSTRATE   3-oxodecanoate [CPD:C20714];
            anthraniloyl-CoA [CPD:C02247];
            malonyl-CoA [CPD:C00083]
PRODUCT     CoA [CPD:C00010];
            2-heptyl-4(1H)-quinolone [CPD:C20643];
            CO2 [CPD:C00011];
            H2O [CPD:C00001];
            4-hydroxy-2(1H)-quinolone [CPD:C16716]
COMMENT     The enzyme from the Gram-negative bacterium Pseudomonas aeruginosa is involved in the biosynthesis of 2-heptyl-4-hydroxyquinoline and 2,4-dihydroxyquinoline. 2-Heptyl-4-hydroxyquinoline is a signal molecule, that is involved in regulation of virulence factor production and biofilm formation. The enzyme shows a broad specificity and is involved in the synthesis of a wide array of additional 2-alkyl-4(1H)-quinolones synthesized by the organism.
